Lucky strike DC is a great spot if you're looking to bowl and/or eat and drink. Prices are reasonable in my opinion. Most recently I've stopped by on a Saturday afternoon for a game and paid about  $24 for two games and the rental of two pairs of shoes. I don't bowl too often but, from what I can remember those prices are fairly standard. Drinks were also reasonably priced. I'll have to try the food the next time. The menu looked decent but, there are a million places to eat in DC so we opted for another. In addition to bowling there are also a couple pool tables, air hockey, dart boards and a few interactive games that you can take part in if you're so inclined to do so. Try and make your reservations well ahead of time because time slots tend to fill up quickly, which can lead to you waiting about an hour or two depending on when you go. All in all my experiences have been great so I'd definitely recommend that you stop by if you're in the area and need a bowling fix.

Terrible service and unreasonable management.  Nachos were delivered to our lane and neither our team nor the team next to us had ordered nachos. We told this to the waitor multiple times but he placed the nachos on our table anyway. We waited for him to come back and remove them since they weren’t ours, but he never did, and there were not any other waitors around to tell. After about 10 minutes we figured it was too late for them to be taken to the correct table anyway so our team and the team next to us decided to eat them since otherwise they would just go to waste.  A few minutes later a waitess came to us and said the nachos were mistakenly delivered and since we didn’t say anything we had to pay for them. We told her repeatedly that we did tell the waitor multiple times. The manager then came and accused us of taking the nachos and not telling anyone they weren’t ours and that we had to pay for them. After a lot of back and forth she said she would take 50% off the nachos. We again said that we did not order nachos, did tell the waitor multiple times that they weren’t part of our order, and should not be forced to pay for something we didn’t order.  Between our two teams, there were 16 people purchasing food and buying drinks, but the staff was completely unreasonable and forced us to pay for their mistake on top of everything else we ordered. Totally unacceptable.

YMMV.  In a 90 minute timeslot, our lane stopped working maybe 10 times, each taking a few minutes to fix. When our time elapsed with just 3 bowlers remaining to clear out our game, we asked for them to let us finish. The screen came back on, we threw a single ball, and the game ended again. Our same group finished a game and a half in the same time just 2 weeks prior without an issue.  When we asked for the lane to get turned on to finish, we were told simply "no." I went to go explain the situation, and the attendant shook his head at me and started to walk away. It's a loud place with the music, so admittedly I may have shouted when the attendant got a few steps out, but all I said was "we lost 30 minutes of our time waiting!"  The attendant turned back and told me not to disrespect him, spent about 30 seconds telling me how he wouldn't take my abuse, how I was wrong, how we started late (we didn't), then threatened to call security on me.  By the time he finished, he asked if I wanted to speak to a manager. By the time that happened, most of our team had left.  I give credit to the staff for, after all that, trying to make it right by offering to give us our last few minutes, but it was too late. You can't bowl a game without the bowlers!  I'm guessing the attendant at the desk probably takes rough clientele all night, since it's an alley and a bar, but this is the first time in 30 years of living I've so much been warned in a public space. I felt my request and tone were pretty reasonable, misunderstandings aside.  I've never been to a single alley in my life that refused to entertain a finished game in the 10th frame, especially when facing technically difficulties. At this one, I feel like I got lectured and shamed for asking.
